= Conclusion

The conclusion should provide a very detailed and insightful account of the achievements and limitations of the project, with excellent reflection on the development process and potential future directions.

== Summary of Findings and Research Questions

Summarise the key findings of your research and explicitly address each of your original research questions. Where applicable, state whether your hypotheses were supported or rejected, and discuss the implications of these findings.

== Achievement of Objectives

Reflect on whether your aims and objectives were met, and to what extent. Revisit each objective stated in the literature review and provide evidence of its completion or explain why it was not fully achieved.

== Limitations

Discuss the limitations of your project, including any constraints that affected the scope, methodology, or results. Being honest about limitations demonstrates critical awareness and strengthens the academic quality of your work.

== Future Work

Discuss potential directions for future research and any improvements that could be made. These should flow naturally from the limitations identified above, as well as from any new questions raised by your findings.
